Left subclavian-pulmonary trunk fistula with a vascular prosthesis as palliative treatment in Fallot conditions. In this paper, our experience with a new systemic-to-pulmonary artery shunt: subclavian-pulmonary artery trunk shunt with PTFE (central shunt) is presented. Between November 1985 and March 1990 this central shunt was employed in 8 children with ages ranged between 4 days and 3 years, and weights between 2 and 12 kg. Diagnosis were Fallot's tetralogy in three pulmonary atresia with intact septum in three